column10: I was crossing with the walk light. It starts at 30, and was down to 25 seconds when a car ran through the red light. The driver slowed down when she saw me, but then proceeded to drive around me.
column21: The walk signal counts down from 30 sec. to 0. The driver entered the intersection when the walk sign was at 25 sec. All other drivers were stopped. This individual was distracted.

column10: There was a long line of cars waiting to turn onto West Taylor Pkwy from west bound Duke St. A driver made a right turn from the second lane from the right narrowly missing a pedestrian crossing Duke St. with the walk light. Another driver had also turned right from the second about 1 min. earlier.
column21: I have noticed and experienced several incidents at this intersection. It has become very dangerous for pedestrians and cyclists particularly during afternoon rush hours.
